sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM eligible_slots 
WHERE slot_position = '1st Batter' AND eligible = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "All-seasoned baseball players" refers to players with extensive experience in the game; 
- "Actively participated" implies playing in more than 100 games in a season; 
- "Offensive prowess" is measured by on-base plus slugging (OPS), a baseball statistic which measures at bats, combining the ability of a player to get on base with the ability to hit for power.
